Salary: Up to $145k Base + Super + Leave Entitlements
Ad Text:
Are you an analyst with a passion for turning data into actionable sales strategies?

We are looking for a Sales Insights Analyst to join a fast-paced, high-growth global SaaS company.

You will dive deep into sales data to identify and communicate growth opportunities, directly influencing the productivity and success of a highly motivated APAC sales team.

What You’ll Be Doing:

Analyse data from Salesforce and other sources to uncover lead, opportunity, and account insights that drive performance and productivity.
Translate complex business needs into clear, actionable data insights to support sales teams across the SMB and Mid-Market segments.
Develop and simplify daily, weekly, and monthly reports on sales pipeline health and its impact on growth, presenting findings to sales leadership.
Measure the success of sales activities and strategic initiatives, providing recommendations for optimisation and improvement.
Partner with the sales team to manage and enhance sales tools and processes, boosting overall effectiveness.
What You Can Bring to the Team:

A proven track record in sales analysis, business analysis, or a similar data-centric role.
Strong experience with Salesforce (Sales Cloud), including building reports and dashboards to track performance.
Advanced skills in Excel or Google Sheets, with the ability to analyse and model data from multiple sources.
A natural ability to translate complex data into clear, compelling insights and recommendations for sales and leadership teams.
A genuine affinity for sales processes and a passion for using data to drive commercial outcomes.
Advanced data skills are a huge plus – SQL, Python, Alteryx, Tableau, or QlikSense.
Why This is the Perfect Time to Join?

Work in a pivotal role where your insights directly impact regional growth for a world-class tech company.
Join a high-energy team that values collaboration, innovation, and data-driven decisions.
Enjoy the flexibility of a hybrid work model while being at the centre of a fast-growing APAC sales operation.
If you’re ready to make a real impact with your analytical skills, apply now!

Scope Systems is a leading supplier of Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP), Business Intelligence (BI) software, Infrastructure Services and associated consulting services to the global mining and other services industries. We offer an exciting, fast paced, fun environment and strive to challenge our employees to achieve their full potential whilst developing long term partnerships with our clients to continually add value and exceed their expectations. 




The Role 

We are seeking a Senior Consultant in the Business Intelligence department at Scope Systems reporting to the Team Lead – Business Intelligence, as a Senior Business Intelligence Consultant you will design, build and maintain enterprise reporting and analytics solutions that deliver trusted, actionable insight to clients. You will be expected to design scalable dimensional models, semantic layers and data marts that support both governed and self-service analytics.  Additionally, you will promote the use of BI products and solutions to Scope Systems’ clients. 

You will be based in our office at West Leederville, however on occasion may require travel to customer sites.   

  

Key Responsibilities 

Lead the design, build and maintenance of enterprise dashboards, reports and semantic models. 

Translate business and stakeholder requirements into technical designs, data models and visualisation concepts. 

Technical expertise across tools and platforms such as Cognos Analytics, Power BI, QlikView and Amazon Quick Sight. 

Lead and facilitate business-facing activities including being able to run workshops, capture requirements, present analysis and proposed solutions to business and senior leaders, and secure buy-in for delivery approaches. 

Provide training and support to clients on the use of BI tools and solutions. 

Stay up-to-date with the latest BI technologies and best practices to continuously improve our offerings. 

Undertake pre sales and business development activities with Account Managers and the Sales team to promote Scope Systems’ BI solutions. 

  

Qualifications & Skills 

Essential 

At 3 least  years of experience as a data and analytics consultant, data analyst, or similar role. 

Experience building end-to-end solutions. 

Strong business analysis skills with the ability to gather and document complex reporting requirements. 

Proficiency in data modelling. 

Proficiency in query languages such as SQL. 

Expertise in extracting, manipulating, and modelling complex data. 

Proficiency with business intelligence tools such as Microsoft Power BI, IBM Cognos Analytics, Amazon Quick Sight, or QlikView. 

Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills, with experience in conducting workshops, briefings, training sessions, presentations, and discussing business intelligence artifacts. 

Advanced knowledge of relational database management systems. 

High level of customer service skills. 

Experience working with a variety of stakeholders. 

A relevant tertiary qualification such as a Bachelor of Computer Science or similar, or relevant industry experience. 




Desirable 

Experience with ERPs ideally Pronto Xi and production mining systems such as Pitram, MPX or Pi Historian.   

Experience with Amazon SageMaker and Quick Sight  

Financial reporting experience. 

Experience working in the mining industry. 

Microsoft Certified: Power BI Data Analyst Associate or relevant industry qualifications. 

Exposure to modelling data for AI.

My client is a leading Financial Services organisation recruiting for a Senior Manager across Markets.
 
Sydney is a preferable location but can consider Melbourne or Brisbane.
 
Duties:-
 
Lead model validation and governance activities across Financial Markets and Treasury portfolios
Partner with business, risk, and technology teams to drive model excellence.
Contribute to key projects and model risk frameworks across the Group
Support and guide junior team members to deliver best-in-class outcomes
 
Requirements:-
 
-6-7+ years’ experience in financial markets quantitative or model risk roles.
Strong understanding of APRA regulatory standards (APS111, APS116, APS117, CPS226, APS180).
-Build or validation across Market Models / FM, counterpart credit risk, derivatives, FX, VAR model traced and non-traded market risk, initial margin. You don't need to be across all of this.
-Proven ability to influence and explain complex concepts to non-technical audiences.
-Programming proficiency in C++, R, or similar languages, with experience using Git or other version control tools.
 
MUST have PR or Citizenship for Australia.
 
Please email me on rupinderk@ethosbc.com.au if you feel you have the relevant experience.
 
I also have Snr Analyst and Manager positions in Markets in other organisations.

Just imagine a future with us...

Aurecon is a design, engineering and advisory company, but not as you know it!

Drawing on our deep pool of technical and advisory expertise, we co-create innovative solutions with our clients to some of the world's most complex challenges. And through a range of unique creative processes and skills, we work to re-imagine, shape and design a better future.

What will you do?

Working with the Queensland / NSW Infrastructure Advisory team and the broader Aurecon Advisory team, this Senior Consultant position offers the opportunity to work on a broad range of consulting projects, providing infrastructure advisory services across a variety of sectors. Here are the things that you will do to bring ideas to life:

Play a lead role in the delivery of services such as business cases, due diligence, technical/commercial advisory services, infrastructure strategy/policy and business improvement drawing in the other expertise of Aurecon
Contribute to the development of client deliverables, including technical reports, client presentations and financial or economic models
Contribute to the identification, development, and conversion of opportunities for future work
Development of proposals responding to client briefs including development of the value proposition, methodology, roles and budgets
Build and maintaining internal and external relationships,
Play an active role in supporting the development of the [Queensland / NSW] Infrastructure Advisory team and fostering a collaborative and inclusive culture of work.

What are we looking for from you?

You'll have passion for re-imagining challenges and continuous learning to shape the future. Ideally you will bring diverse experiences and demonstrate how you work collaboratively to bring ideas to life.

A tertiary qualification in economics, business, finance, public policy, engineering or related degree/discipline
Strong research, analytical and problem-solving skills.
High level of verbal and written communication, including public presentation skills.
Effective planning & organising skills.
Adaptability & flexibility in working with, and across, teams and functions.
A professional commitment to striving for excellence.
A track record of project delivery in a consulting, industry or government environment, preferably with sector experience in at least one of the following: digital infrastructure, transport, water, Defence, energy and resources

Our Aurecon Attributes describe the types of people we bring together for our clients. We don't expect you to have all eight of the attributes, but one that is unique to you.

Diversity is at the core of everything we do. We work together to create a culture based on respect, trust, and inclusiveness. Our differences are what fuel our creativity.

Finally, we value that each of our team members brings something different to Aurecon. We look for people who have had a broad range of experiences throughout their career and can demonstrate how they have worked as part of a team to bring ideas to life.

Does that sound like you? APPLY NOW!

Opportunity:

The Business Analyst is a key member of the PMO team, responsible for bridging the gap between business needs and technology solutions. Working collaboratively with project teams and stakeholders, the role provides business analysis and project coordination support to ensure successful delivery of project outcomes.

Key responsibilities

Identifying, analysing, and documenting business requirements using appropriate business analysis techniques,
Communicating these requirements clearly to a diverse range of stakeholders in a financial services organisation.
Supporting the delivery of initiatives such as technology implementations and enhancements, operational improvement activities, audit remediation, procurement processes, and supplier engagement.
Provide project coordination support for smaller projects and operational improvement initiatives.

About You

Ideally you will be an experience Business Analyst, with a background in financial services and the following skills:

Extensive experience leading technical business activities in a project setting, preferably within medium to large complex organisations. (public sector and/or finance industry experience highly desirable) 
Experience in the application of business analysis frameworks and techniques, such as BABOK.
Experience in contributing to business and technology change activities, including the development and implementation of new systems, processes, and practices.
Experience in treasury management and/or treasury systems within a financial services environment.
Partnering closely with Architecture & Solution Design to ensure business requirements align with enterprise technical design principles.
Leading “as-is” and “to-be” process design and supporting organisational change impact analysis.

This organisation is well regarded and has an outstanding reputation. Join the PMO for a 1 year fixed term contract and get an opportunity to work some exciting projects.

Apply Now as we are moving quickly with hiring for this role. For any queries contact Max Mutakiwa on 0417 053 161.

Senior Analyst – Asset Management
CapitaLand Australia | Sydney | Institutional Real Estate Funds Platform

Take ownership of performance and strategy across a diversified institutional property portfolio.

CapitaLand Australia is seeking a Senior Analyst – Asset Management to play a key role in driving asset performance, delivering strategic insights and supporting value creation initiatives across our Australian portfolio of office, logistics, business space and lodging assets.

This is a high-impact role suited to an experienced property or funds professional looking to step into greater responsibility within a global real estate investment manager.

About CapitaLand
CapitaLand Australia manages approximately S$8 billion of assets locally and forms part of CapitaLand Investment, one of Asia’s largest real estate investment managers with S$125 billion+ AUM globally across listed REITs and private funds.

The Role
Working closely with the Head of Asset Management and regional portfolio teams in Australia and Singapore, you will take the lead on portfolio analysis, reporting, financial modelling and strategic asset initiatives that directly influence investment outcomes.

You will be a trusted partner to Asset Managers, Finance and external stakeholders, providing the insights and rigour required to optimise asset value and performance.

Key Responsibilities

Lead monthly asset and portfolio performance reporting and analysis
Own budgeting, forecasting and business planning processes
Build and maintain detailed cash flow and valuation models
Provide commercial analysis to support leasing, capex and repositioning decisions
Prepare and present Strategic Asset Plans and investment papers
Monitor asset performance against benchmarks and market conditions
Manage sustainability/ESG performance data and reporting
Coordinate annual valuations, audits and due diligence processes
Drive improvements to systems, reporting tools and data integrity
Partner with internal and external stakeholders to execute asset strategies
About You

Degree in Real Estate, Property, Finance, Commerce or similar
3–6+ years’ experience in asset management, funds management, valuations, property finance or investment analysis
Strong financial modelling capability and commercial judgement
Advanced Excel skills; ARGUS/MRI/Forbury highly regarded
Comfortable taking ownership and working directly with senior stakeholders
Detail-oriented with the ability to manage multiple deadlines in a fast-paced environment
Why Join CapitaLand Australia

Institutional-quality assets and sophisticated capital platform
High visibility and direct exposure to senior leadership
Regional collaboration with Singapore and global teams
Strong career progression within a leading real estate investment manager
Apply by sending your resume to ben@redpathpartners.com or reach out to Ben Gregg at Redpath Partners on 0415919590 for a confidential discussion.

Adobe Martech Analytics Lead - Melbourne

As the Adobe Martech Analytics Lead, you will work closely with technical and business stakeholders to design, implement, and optimise analytics solutions that drive measurable digital performance and customer insights.



Key Responsibilities
Lead end-to-end Adobe CJA and Adobe Analytics implementations
Design analytics solutions aligned to client strategy, use cases, and industry standards
Implement and manage Adobe/Google Analytics tagging across web and mobile platforms
Debug and troubleshoot Adobe data collection and tracking issues
Create, validate, and interpret segments, events, and custom tracking logic
Build custom reports and dashboards to deliver actionable insights
Gather, document, and guide business requirements, KPIs, and technical needs
Train and enable clients on analytics platforms and best practices
Leverage data to improve digital performance, reach, and ROI
Guide teams and clients throughout the full project lifecycle

Job Title: Senior Business Analyst - Contact Centre Uplift
Ad Text:
Will you actively create a healthier future for tomorrow?

At Medibank we're encouraged to think big. We have a clear purpose to impact better health outcomes for our customers, patients and our community.



We celebrate diversity of thought because we want to make better decisions for our customers. As we work towards our goal of better health for better lives, we value the knowledge and contribution of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islanders. We are working hard to create an inclusive workplace and develop Indigenous careers.

Medibank has bold 2030 Vision to deliver the best health and wellbeing for Australia increasingly relies on succeeding in Digital. Digital platforms and engineering services will be a critical enabler for future health and insurance experiences we deliver to our customers. The current Digital platforms have strong capabilities but for us to win in the context of 2030 vision, our digital assets will need to be reimagined and further evolved that is scalable, increases agility and accelerate solution delivery with improved security posture. 

About the role We're embarking on a major multi‑brand transformation of our contact centre technology environment through a large‑scale CCaaS uplift, modernising telephony across all brands by moving from legacy on‑premise systems to a contemporary cloud platform. This program spans shaping, discovery, vendor evaluation, delivery and post-go‑live optimisation across telephony, IVR, call routing, reporting, analytics and user configuration, ultimately simplifying our tech landscape, strengthening reliability and improving member experience. We are seeking a high‑performing, confident and outcome‑driven Senior Business Analyst with deep contact centre expertise to join us on a $900/day, six‑month contract with strong potential for extension, leading requirements and discovery across all telephony and contact centre streams in a fast‑paced, multi‑brand environment; please note this is a highly specialised role and applicants should apply only if they meet the majority of the criteria.


What You'll Lead
Requirements across telephony, IVR, queues, routing, call flows and configuration
User roles, permissions and operational processes
Reporting and analytics requirements
Functional and non‑functional requirements aligned to CCaaS constraints
As‑is and to‑be telephony, reporting and operational process documentation
Vendor assessment, capability reviews and RFP support
MVP‑focused simplification to drive quick, effective decision‑making
Alignment across brands, infrastructure and call flow workstreams
Clear, concise impact summaries and contribution to program governance


What You'll Bring
Deep experience in contact centre operations and CCaaS platforms
Strong understanding of telephony technologies (Genesys, NICE, AWS Connect or similar)
Experience with on‑prem → cloud telephony migrations
Knowledge of IVR logic, routing rules and telephony terminology
Background in operational/transactional reporting requirements
Ability to work across PMs, SMEs, operational leaders and vendors
Confidence to challenge, align and clarify in ambiguous environments
Practical, outcome‑focused approach — avoids over‑documenting
Fast, autonomous working style; proactive "go‑getter" mentality
Strong change awareness and understanding of user impacts

Before You Apply

This is a very specialised Senior BA role with a strong telephony and CCaaS focus. Please apply only if you meet most of the criteria below.



A career with us


At Medibank, we believe work is something we do, not somewhere we go. Our modes of working - Collaboration, Connection and Concentration - help inform how your day is structured and where you choose to work will vary, depending on your role and requirements.  


The wellbeing of our employees is our priority. We encourage you to talk to us about any additional support you may require during the recruitment process, as well as how this role can be flexible for you. We encourage applications from candidates with a disability, if you require any adjustments or alternate formats of key information at any stage of the recruitment process, we welcome hearing from you.

About Zembl:

Zembl saves businesses time and improves their bottom line. Our long, strong industry relationships help businesses buy better energy. We have local experts who'll pick up the phone, have a chat and understand customer needs to take the legwork out of admin. Our simple digital platform and helpful people make admin easy, even pleasurable.

Purpose of the role:

As our Pricing Manager, you'll play a critical role in shaping Zembl's commercial success. Sitting within our Product & Operations team, you'll lead pricing strategy, optimise margins and ensure our offers are competitive, accurate and aligned to market conditions.

This is a high-impact role where commercial thinking meets operational precision. You'll collaborate closely with Sales, Finance and Leadership to ensure our pricing approach supports sustainable growth while delivering value to our customers.

About You

You're commercially minded, detail-oriented and confident working with numbers. You enjoy balancing strategy with execution and thrive in an environment where you can influence outcomes.

Visa sponsorship is available for qualified candidates who do not hold Australian work rights.

You bring:

Proven experience in pricing, commercial analysis or a similar analytical role

A minimum of 3-4 years of experience in pricing or commercial analysis roles

Strong financial and commercial acumen with the ability to interpret complex data

Advanced Excel skills and confidence working with large data sets

Proficiency in Power Query/BI for advanced data analysis and reporting

Ability to build pricing models and provide clear recommendations

High attention to detail with strong governance and risk awareness

Excellent stakeholder management skills across Sales, Finance and Operations

Clear communicator who can translate numbers into meaningful insights

Experience in energy, utilities or related commercial environment (desirable)

A Bachelors' degree in Commerce, Economics, Finance, Engineering, Data or Maths

Key Responsibilities

Develop and manage pricing strategies that support revenue growth and margin optimisation

Build, maintain and refine pricing models and tools

Analyse market trends, competitor positioning and cost inputs

Partner with Sales to structure commercially sound customer offers

Work closely with Finance to ensure pricing aligns with financial targets

Monitor pricing performance and identify improvement opportunities

Ensure pricing governance, controls and documentation are maintained

Provide insights and reporting to senior stakeholders

Work day-to-day with Partnerships to operationalise partner pricing

Lead pricing readiness for major reforms

Benefits:

The Templ of Zembl is full of a positive vibe of music, laughter and celebrating achievements. You hear the enthusiasm and feel a part of it. It means we actually love coming to work. How good's that?

Hybrid work-from-home and in-office approach, plus 20 days each year to work from anywhere in the world

2 wellness days per year to rest and recharge

1 volunteer leave day per year to support causes that matter to you

Anniversary leave rewards – earn extra leave the longer you stay (up to 5 days)

Career progression opportunities with homegrown leaders

Up to 16 weeks paid parental leave

Daily perks including 1 free coffee from the onsite barista and a monthly Uber Eats lunch allowance

About Us

Join us at Cleanaway and contribute to making a sustainable future possible, together. We transform waste into resources and renewable energy.  When you start to think of waste as a resource, it opens a world of possibilities.

As a high growth, ASX listed organisation with over 10,000 employees, our goal is to be recognised by our customers as the most innovative and sustainable waste management company with industry leading HSE performance.  We are Australia’s largest company in this sector, providing essential services to millions of customers and communities nationally.

The Opportunity

Reporting into the Customer & Commercial function, this newly created role is responsible for establishing Cleanaway’s enterprise supply and demand forecasting capability.

What You Will Be Doing

• Establish and own the enterprise supply and demand forecasting framework used across the business
• Develop macro-to-micro forecasting models spanning enterprise, business unit, regional, branch and route levels
• Provide scenario modelling and forward-looking insights to inform pricing strategy, budgeting, re-forecasting and capital investment
• Challenge and escalate growth plans, pricing actions and CAPEX proposals where assumptions do not stack up
• Translate complex analytical outputs into decision-ready insights for GM and executive forums
• Uplift forecasting standards, governance and capability across a matrixed, multi-site organisation

About You

You are a highly analytical, commercially minded professional who thrives in complex, asset-driven environments. You are comfortable operating at enterprise scale while influencing decisions that impact network utilisation, investment and long-term value.

What You Bring

• Strong background in forecasting, economics, actuarial analysis, applied statistics or quantitative modelling
• Proven experience building and applying advanced forecasting models in large, complex organisations
• Hands-on capability with statistical and modelling tools such as Python, R, SPSS, Minitab, Power BI and advanced Excel
• Experience working in asset-intensive, network-constrained industries such as utilities, logistics, infrastructure, manufacturing or waste
• Confidence challenging assumptions and influencing senior commercial, operational and finance leaders
• Ability to translate complex data into clear, practical insights that drive better business decisions

Qualifications

• Tertiary qualification in economics, actuarial studies, statistics, data science, business or a related discipline
• Experience working within a large, matrixed, asset-driven organisation is highly regarded

Why join Cleanaway

Attractive salary package
Career development opportunities
Paid parental leave
Great company benefits: Annual employee share plan offer, novated leasing, optional flu vaccinations, EAP access, discounts on private health insurance, company discounts + much more! 

Our Process

Our recruitment process involves a number of checks including, but not limited to, criminal history, medicals, drug & alcohol testing, as well as verification of qualifications, licences and right-to-work status.

All internal applicants will receive a notification within 2 weeks of the closing date of this advertisement.  

We are dedicated to improving employment outcomes and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. We also welcome candidates of all ages, abilities, gender identities, experiences (including veterans), and cultural backgrounds.

If you require any adjustments during the recruitment process, please contact us by emailing inclusion@cleanaway.com.au.

Join us on our exciting journey towards a sustainable future.

Simply click the Apply button or visit https://www.cleanaway.com.au/about-us/careers and let's make a positive impact together.

#LI-Hybrid
#LI-MB1

We’ve been proudly serving Australian communities since 1914 and have grown to become a top 30-listed company on the ASX with a portfolio of iconic homegrown brands. At the heart of our continued success is over 115,000 team members working across the country, all contributing to bringing our customers smiles. You’ll not only get to see your work make a difference, you’ll be part of a team working together to help Australians eat and live better every day.

 

About the team

 

As the way Australians shop continues to evolve, our Data and AI Team keep Coles at the forefront of modern retail. We combine data, artificial intelligence, and applied engineering to reimagine how our stores, supply chain, and digital channels operate — creating smarter, more connected, and seamless experiences for our customers and team members.

 

Operating as a centralised development and enablement function within Coles Technology, the team unites product, engineering, and platform capabilities to deliver the intelligence layer of the enterprise. We serve every part of Coles — from computer vision applications that enhance in-store experiences and reduce loss, to forecasting, optimisation, and decision-support solutions that drive efficiency, accuracy, and agility across our supply chain, retail operations, and corporate functions.

 

The scale and impact of this work are significant. Coles serves millions of customers each week across more than a thousand stores nationwide, and our AI and data capabilities provide the intelligence that underpins how we plan, move, sell, and serve. By combining deep data capability with applied AI and modern engineering, we’re enabling Coles to become a truly AI-enabled enterprise, transforming how we operate and how Australia shops every day.



About the role

 

As Transformation Manager for Enablement, reporting into the Senior Platform Manager for Transformation and Modernisation, your primary function will be to Lead the development and ongoing refinement of the transformation roadmap across data platforms, AI capabilities, and enterprise reporting, ensuring it reflects evolving business needs and technology trends.

 

Your main responsibilities will include the following but not be limited to the below: 

 

Ensure roadmap alignment with enterprise strategy, business priorities, and technology architecture, integrating inputs from business units, IT, and leadership.
Facilitate prioritisation of initiatives based on business impact, technical feasibility, risk profile, and organisational readiness.
Work with stakeholders to define and track transformation value outcomes, including cost savings, operational efficiency, improved decision-making, and enhanced customer experience.
Build and socialize business cases for transformation initiatives, including cost-benefit analysis, risk assessment, and ROI projections to secure executive sponsorship and funding.
Collaborate with Finance, Strategy, and Architecture teams to ensure alignment, endorsement, and integration into broader enterprise planning cycles.
Act as a strategic partner to business and technology stakeholders, ensuring clarity of purpose, shared ownership, and sustained commitment to transformation outcomes
Ensure transparency and traceability of decisions, priorities, and outcomes, through structured governance forums, reporting frameworks, and stakeholder communications.
Embed continuous improvement mechanisms into the roadmap, leveraging feedback loops, performance data, and lessons learned to refine priorities and accelerate value delivery.
Develop and maintain a transformation roadmap dashboard, providing real-time visibility into progress, risks, dependencies, and business outcomes for executive stakeholders.

 

 
About you and your skills

 

Proven years of progressive experience in enterprise technology, platform management, or IT transformation leadership roles.
Led the creation and continuous refinement of enterprise-wide transformation roadmaps across data platforms, AI capabilities, and reporting ecosystems, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities, enterprise architecture, and long-term business goals.
Built and championed high-impact business cases for transformation initiatives, incorporating cost-benefit analysis, ROI modelling, risk assessments, and stakeholder endorsement to secure funding and executive sponsorship.
Successfully influenced and engaged senior leaders across business, technology, finance, and strategy, driving shared ownership of transformation outcomes and embedding data-driven thinking into strategic planning.
Established governance frameworks and executive reporting, ensuring transparency, traceability of decisions, and proactive escalation of risks and issues.
Defined and tracked transformation success metrics, including adoption rates, data quality improvements, NPS, and business impact, using insights to refine delivery approaches and accelerate value realisation.
Identified and managed cross-functional dependencies, resource requirements, and initiative sequencing to ensure realistic, achievable, and integrated transformation delivery plans.
Acted as a strategic advisor to executives, translating complex technical initiatives into business outcomes and guiding investment decisions across data and AI domains.
Directed and facilitated Quarterly Planning cycles, aligning cross-functional teams on transformation priorities, dependencies, and delivery commitments across business and technology domains

 

 

Skills and Qualifications

 

Excellent interpersonal and communication skills to influence, align, and collaborate with senior leaders, cross-functional teams, and external partners.
Proficiency in building business cases, conducting cost-benefit analyses, and defining measurable value outcomes such as ROI, efficiency gains, and adoption metrics.
Strong strategic thinking and problem-solving skills with a business and technology mindset.
Understanding of cloud platforms (Azure, Snowflake, Databricks), containerisation (Docker, Kubernetes), and automation tools (Terraform, Ansible).

 

 

Education:

 

Bachelor’s or Master’s Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Systems or related discipline. Advanced certifications in cloud platforms or transformation management are a plus.

 

 

 

 

 



What’s in it for you?

 

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

TDPS Finance Analyst

Fed Gov - aviation sector / 12-month contract
Brisbane Airport + WFH (3 days in office) - free onsite parking
Australian Citizens holding, or eligible to hold, a National Security Clearance
The Opportunity

The Technical Delivery Portfolio (TDP) delivers a broad suite of programs and projects to modernise operational (mission-critical) and corporate networks. These initiatives ensure the continuity of safe, efficient and effective Air Navigation and Aviation Rescue and Fire Fighting services, while enabling future capability enhancements including CMATS, Remote Service Delivery and Flexible Use of Airspace.

The Technology Delivery Portfolio Services (TDPS) function is expanding to strengthen PMO capability across the portfolio. Reporting to the TDPS Finance & Performance Lead, the Finance Analyst will drive the implementation and embedding of established PMO financial models, processes and reporting frameworks across the Technology Delivery Portfolio.

This is a hands-on role where you will also provide direct financial support to programs and projects during this uplift and standardisation phase.

Key Responsibilities

Financial Management & Portfolio Reporting

Implement and embed TDPS financial models, processes and reporting across the Technology Delivery Portfolio
Review and standardise existing portfolio financial models into TDPS formats
Establish reporting templates and consolidation mechanisms for portfolio-level management reporting
Implement and manage the financial management cadence across programs and projects
Financial Control & Governance

Manage month-end processes including forecasting, variance analysis and complex contract financial updates
Prepare financial reporting for senior stakeholders including Executive leadership, CFO, ePMO and Boards
Develop and maintain financial plans, budgets and forecasts (CAPEX and OPEX)
Support financial controls for the TDPS budget
Maintain and update Work Breakdown Structures in SAP
Process project forecast uploads in SAP
Support vendor contract financial management and payment tracking
Provide financial modelling input into Business Cases and Change Impact Assessments
Stakeholder & Team Contribution

Build strong relationships across Corporate Finance, Business Planning & Performance, Portfolio Leadership and Project Managers
Collaborate with Managed Service Providers and third-party vendors
Contribute to a high-performance, accountable team culture
Support continuous improvement in financial processes and service delivery
Governance & Compliance

Comply with enterprise governance frameworks including Safety, Risk, WHS and Environmental policies
Demonstrate safety-first behaviours aligned with organisational strategy
About You

You are a proactive and commercially minded finance professional with experience supporting large-scale project environments. You thrive in complex, fast-paced settings and are confident engaging with senior stakeholders.

Essential Experience & Skills:

4–5+ years’ experience in Financial Analysis or similar role within a project delivery environment
Tertiary qualification in Accounting, Finance or related discipline (or equivalent experience)
Strong experience in budgeting, forecasting and reporting for large programs (>$100m)
Experience tracking vendor contract payments and managing financial controls
Advanced capability in Microsoft Excel
Intermediate experience in Microsoft Power BI, SAP and Microsoft Project/Project Server
Strong communication, stakeholder engagement and interpersonal skills
Demonstrated resilience and ability to deliver under pressure
Proven ability to translate strategic direction into practical financial processes and improvements
Eligibility:

Australian Citizens holding, or eligible to hold, a National Security Clearance
Work From Home Policy:

Hybrid (3 days in office) - free onsite parking
Rate:

Up to $850.00 per day inc Super

What's the role?

This is a permanent opportunity for a Program Manager to lead the end-to-end program delivery of high-impact strategic initiatives for The Australian and Prestige. Based in our Surry Hills office with flexible working arrangements, you will shape the digital customer experience, accelerate audience growth, and optimise commercial outcomes.

Reporting to the Head of Marketing and Program Management, you will unite cross-functional teams around clear objectives, delivering measurable results through disciplined governance, data-led decision-making, and high-quality execution.

What You’ll Do

Understand the Australian & Prestige audience growth strategy and lead the delivery of aligned strategic initiatives.

Own end-to-end program delivery across digital experience, consumer growth, and commercial priorities, with clear governance, success metrics, and integrated delivery plans.

Lead cross-functional teams across product, data, marketing, editorial, and commercial functions to deliver outcomes on time and within budget.

Embed a customer-centric, data-led approach using insights, experimentation, and measurement frameworks to drive ROI and continuous improvement.

Drive change management and adoption through stakeholder engagement, communications, training, operational readiness, and rollout plans that sustain outcomes.

Proactively identify and manage risks, issues, and assumptions; maintain RAID logs, ensure compliance with Australian privacy, spam, and consumer laws, and uphold brand safety.

Support go-to-market readiness and execution as required.

Who are you?

10+ years’ experience leading complex digital product and marketing programs, delivering consumer growth and commercial outcomes.

Proven ability to manage multiple concurrent initiatives in fast-paced, complex environments.

Strong expertise in program governance, benefits realisation, and hybrid delivery (Agile/Waterfall).

Advanced data literacy, with experience in analytics, experimentation, attribution, and ROI measurement.

Demonstrated leadership of cross-functional teams and vendors, with strong executive stakeholder management.

Solid financial acumen, including budget ownership and commercial negotiation.

Working knowledge of martech, CRM/CDP, product analytics, and Australian regulatory requirements.

Tertiary qualifications in Business, Marketing, Technology or related discipline are desirable.

An established program manager with strong influencing skills.

About the Business

Welcome to Yancoal. For 20 years, we have been supporting the prosperity of Australia. With over 4,500 people working across our operations, our team is made up of experts in their field. The Senior Business Development Analyst is responsible for supporting the commercial and financial analyses of, and input into, important business decisions such as acquisitions, joint ventures, divestments and major capital investments. Duties include, but are not limited to:

Provide key insights and analysis to assist with commercial decision-making.
Financial modelling across the broad suite of investment decisions listed above.

Research on industry, competitors and products that are relevant to current or potential business opportunities

Support the life of mine, strategic planning and short-term planning systems and processes for the business

Bachelor's degree: economics, engineering, finance or accounting
Experience in commercial and business analysis activities in a mining environment a plus
Exposure to M&A activities desirable.
Advanced skills in sophisticated financial modelling.
Strong commercial acumen, including understanding of accounting concepts.
Experience with due diligence activities
Ability to present confidently to senior stakeholders throughout the business
Expert in Microsoft products especially Excel.
Strong verbal and written communication skills
Demonstrated skills in continuous improvement activities

The Business Insights & Data Interpretation Manager will play a key role in driving data-driven decision-making within the Technology department of the Transport & Distribution industry. This temporary role based in Melbourne requires a strong ability to analyse and interpret data to provide actionable insights.

Client Details

This opportunity is with a well-established organisation in the Transport & Distribution sector. They are a medium-sized company known for their commitment to innovation and operational excellence in Melbourne.

Description

Analyse complex datasets to uncover trends and actionable insights.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business needs and provide data-driven solutions.
Develop and maintain dashboards and reporting tools to support decision-making.
Ensure data integrity and accuracy through thorough validation and quality checks.
Communicate findings and recommendations clearly to stakeholders.
Support the Technology department with predictive and prescriptive analytics.

Profile

A successful Business Insights & Data Interpretation Manager should have:

Strong analytical skills with experience in data interpretation and insights generation.
Strong experience using Power BI to interpret and consume business insights.
Advanced Excel skills.
Knowledge of the Transport & Distribution industry is advantageous.
Excellent communication skills to present findings effectively.
A proactive approach to problem-solving and identifying opportunities for improvement.
Ability to collaborate with diverse teams and stakeholders.
Proven experience in maintaining data quality and integrity.

Job Offer

Opportunity to contribute to impactful projects in the Transport & Distribution industry.
Be part of a collaborative and supportive team in Melbourne.
Temporary role offering flexibility and career development opportunities.

If you are passionate about leveraging data to drive business success, we encourage you to apply for the Business Insights & Data Interpretation Manager position in Melbourne today!
